@himanshug See if the following PR fixes it for you in 0.6 https://github.com/druid-io/druid/pull/957/files
Just adding the line here should fix your issue: https://github.com/druid-io/druid/pull/957/files#diff-564b553ed0071ba9c897abf6a7ca8b8fR129, but if you also want to have gzip compression for POST requests, you will need this as well https://github.com/druid-io/druid/pull/957/files#diff-f7b24049b9788368c23c082e1cb63e15R32

I'm rewriting the async query proxy servlet as we speak to remove the copy/pasted code from the jetty codebase, now that jetty has better methods to allow overriding, which should allow us to benefit from all the fixes in Jetty.

